    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 showcases the legendary E46 platform, powered by the S54 3.2L inline-six engine featuring individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS high-pressure variable valve timing. The high-revving powerplant is mated to a tactile 6-speed manual transmission, delivering power to the rear wheels via an M Variable Differential Lock. Mechanically sound, this example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including rod bearing replacement and rear subframe reinforcement, ensuring the chassis's torsional rigidity remains intact. The suspension geometry provides the telepathic turn-in these cars are known for, with well-sorted damping and consistent braking performance. While it shows honest patina from careful road use, its mechanical heart and structural health make it a premier driver's car.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 18
    },
    {
