      "description": "Available is a 2011 Porsche Cayman S (987.2), a standout example of mid-engine engineering featuring the 3.4L flat-six with Direct Fuel Injection (DFI). This powerplant delivers 320 hp through a desirable 6-speed manual transaxle, providing a visceral connection to the road that modern EPS systems cannot replicate. The chassis benefits from Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) and a factory-spec limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal turn-in and corner-exit traction. Recent maintenance includes a comprehensive cooling system refresh and a brake fluid flush using high-boiling-point DOT 4. While the exterior shows honest patina consistent with a well-loved driver, the mechanical synchronization of the drivetrain and the tactile feedback of the hydraulic steering rack remain sharp and communicative. This is a performance-first machine ready for the canyons.",
